{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase paternity leave to at least 4 weeks fully paid leave",
        "additional_details": "2 weeks paid leave (which can be at a reduced rate) isn\u2019t sufficient for fathers to bond with their newborns and support their partners.\r\n \r\nIn cases with traumatic birth or even C sections mothers may not even be able to move properly and they need their partners at home.\r\n \r\nSome EU countries already have substantially more generous paternity leave arrangements for new fathers.\r\n \r\nIt isn\u2019t a case of reducing maternity leave so paternity leave is longer, but granting new rights to fathers, which should also help mental and physical well-being for mothers.",
        "background": "Increase paternity leave from 2 weeks (on potentially reduced pay) to at least 4 weeks fully paid leave, to allow them to support new mothers and better bond with their newborns.",
